parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure (DRL Module, Wiring, and Computer Issues)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the Daytime Running Lights (DRL) to malfunction, leading to a potential fire hazard, and also affect the vehicle's overall safety and performance.
symptoms: The DRL lights glow at first and gradually reach full intensity
the headlights go completely out for about 6 seconds before coming on gradually
the airbag light and service engine light are illuminated
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine light starts flashing
and the vehicle's speed drops.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving on the highway, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
the engine light starts flashing
the speed drops
and the vehicle's acceleration is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag and ABS systems can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light and ABS light are illuminated
and the vehicle's safety features are compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or even death in the event of a crash, as the airbags may not deploy properly or at all.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger airbag off light stays on
the airbag fails to deploy in a crash
the airbag sensor is faulty
corrosion on the airbag connector.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Failure to Restart
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling and failure to restart can cause the vehicle to lose power and stall in the middle of the road, increasing the risk of accidents and leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine stalls while in motion or at idle
the engine turns over but has a hard time restarting
the engine attains high RPMs due to late shifting
the engine light comes on during stalling and turns off after 24 hours.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel injection system can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the fuel injection system fails
the engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine catches on fire
heavy front-end damage occurs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body and MAP Sensor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body and MAP sensors can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the throttle body and MAP sensors fail
the engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vapor lock and limp mode can cause the engine to lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The engine goes into limp mode
the vehicle experiences a temporary loss of power
the engine has a vapor lock.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to hesitate or stall when shifting, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It can also cause the vehicle to fail to accelerate, making it difficult to merge or climb hills.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates when shifting
the vehicle fails to accelerate
the vehicle stalls when accelerating from a stop
the transmission shifter does not engage in park completely
the vehicle makes a loud "clunk" or "clink" when shifting
the vehicle accelerates slowly or hard
the vehicle does not shift out of first gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission range sensor can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to hesitation or stalling when shifting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle makes a loud "clunk" or "clink" when shifting
the vehicle accelerates slowly or hard
the vehicle does not shift out of first gear
the transmission range sensor code P0705 appears on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shifter can cause the driver to be unsure if the vehicle is in park, making it difficult to remove the key from the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission shifter does not engage in park completely
the driver is unsure if the vehicle is in park
unable to remove key from vehicle.
